7) Recommending data management solutions.
8) Evaluating and recommending statistical software.
Requirements
A master's degree in statistics or biostatistics or a closely related field. Experience applying statistical methods to experimental design and optimization of biological experiments, preferably in a business setting. Training in and experience using linear models, non-linear models, power calculations, non-parametric methods, longitudinal models, general linear models, and combinatorial design of experiments with many factors. Excellent written and spoken English and demonstrated ability to communicate statistical ideas to non-statisticians. Demonstrated ability to work independently. Proficiency in use of R for statistical computing.
